|YKB                        MONK CHALLENGES
|GKB~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ ~ 

|CK0  Monks must go through challenges throughout their life, to
|CK0  insure that they are ready to move up.

|CK0  Currently, in order to get their next fighting style, they must
|CK0  complete mastery challenges in order to advance to guild level
|CK0  5, 10, 15 and 20.

|CK0  Monk XP continues to accumulate while a trial is incomplete. Completing
|CK0  the trial immediately releases every rank your banked Monk XP and regular
|CK0  level permit.

|CK0  Dragon Rebind becomes available at guild level 19 as the graduation
|CK0  technique for the final mastery trial. Full Dragon style remains the
|CK0  reward for reaching guild level 20.

|CK0  These are no longer simple duels. Each trial asks you to prove
|CK0  that you understand a sequence of forms. The early trials focus
|CK0  on one style at a time, while the final trial demands that you
|CK0  flow through several styles in order.

|CK0  The mastery trial now expects a true bridge chain rather than a
|CK0  handful of manual stance swaps. A successful monk will move from
|CK0  Crane into Monkey, from Monkey into Snake, and from Snake into
|CK0  Tiger without letting the form collapse.

|CK0  Be forewarned, challenges are real. At any time you can "escape"
|CK0  the challenge, but with a penalty.

|CK0  Watch your monk monitor during a trial. It now reports the current
|CK0  trial objective directly, so you can tell whether the chamber is
|CK0  asking for a style swap, a bridge, or a finisher.

